  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the onion, carrot, and celery, and saut\u00166 until tender, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the garlic and cook for another minute.",
    "Add the khus khus and cook for 2-3 minutes, until lightly toasted.",
    "Pour in the vegetable broth and water, and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for 15-20 minutes, or until the khus khus is tender.",
    "Season with salt and black pepper to taste.",
    "Stir in the dried dill.",
    "Spoon the pilaf into mason jars and serve.",
    "Refrigerate or freeze for later use."
